summary:
Tony Stark's left arm has consistently been hurt through the Marvel movies.
(Probably from getting shot by a tank there in his...
body:
Infinity War part 2

Tony Stark’s left arm has consistently been hurt through the Marvel movies.

(Probably from getting shot by a tank there in his fight at Golmeda)

Thanos’ Infinity Gauntlet is on his left arm and it’s all busted up at the end.

Lookin’ like some nasty beef jerky with his ol’ raisin ass.

So my theory is that Tony gets the Infinity Gauntlet (on his left hand) and snaps, setting the universe back at peace and giving up his life in the process.

summary: So, like, Peggy Carter is basically the foundations for the entirety of the marvel universe. She had faith that Steve could make...
body:
So, like, Peggy Carter is basically the foundations for the entirety of the marvel universe. She had faith that Steve could make it back with the soldier, she tells him in Winter Soldier that “sometimes the best we can do is to start over”, and Sharon’s speech at her funeral solidifies Steve’s resolution against the accords.

She not only created Shield, but she okied it’s destruction and essentially gave her blessing to “Team Cap”, without whom Infinity War could have taken place without the war in Wakanda, but by simply ripping out the mind stone from Vision while he and Wanda are together at the beginning.

She emplified the sincerity of Captain America back when he was just tiny skimpy heartfelt do-right Steve Rogers, and so even when he came back 70 years later and he could have become jaded and angry and vengeful, he didn’t. He stayed the Cap she knew because he was not a perfect soldier, but a good man, and because he knew that Peggy would demand and accept nothing less then the guy who does what’s right, not what’s smart or self-preserving
